  "prompt": "How do I remove a non-friend from Facebook messenger contact list?",
  "response": "Removing a non-friend from your Facebook Messenger contact list can help declutter your chat list. Here\u2019s how you can do it:\n\n### **On Mobile (iOS/Android):**\n1. Open the **Facebook Messenger app**.\n2. Tap on the **Chats** icon at the bottom.\n3. Scroll or search for the person you want to remove.\n4. Long-press on their chat or tap and hold their name.\n5. Select **Delete Chat** or **Remove** (options may vary by device).\n6. Confirm by tapping **Delete** or **Remove**.\n\nIf you want to archive the chat instead of deleting it:\n- Swipe left on the chat and tap the **Archive** option.\n\n### **On Desktop:**\n1. Open **Facebook Messenger** in your browser or the desktop app.\n2. Find the chat with the person you want to remove.\n3. Hover over the chat and click the **three dots (\u00b7\u00b7\u00b7)** or **gear icon** next to their name.\n4. Select **Delete Chat** or **Remove.\n5. Confirm the action.\n\n### **Preventing Them from Messaging You Again:**\nIf you want to ensure they cannot message you again:\n1. Open the chat with the person.\n2. Tap on their name at the top of the chat.\n3. Scroll down and select **Block** or **Report** (if necessary).\n   - **Block** will prevent them from contacting you entirely.\n   - **Report** is for inappropriate behavior.\n\n### **Note:**\n- Removing someone from your Messenger list doesn\u2019t block them. They can still message you unless you block them.\n- If the person is not your Facebook friend, they\u2019ll remain in your Messenger list if you\u2019ve interacted with them before. Deleting the chat simply removes the conversation from your view.\n\nLet me know if you need further assistance!",
  "temperature": 1.0,
